race.comment: ELITE FIGHTER (1) was unplaced when fresh from a spell, then settled well back and finished three lengths away in eighth over 1400m at Ascot a fortnight ago. He will be peaking third up, and drops right down in class here. On top this time. CHEROKEE MISS (2) has been battling to find some good form and will be on a 5-day backup in this. She is capable of better, and in this class, a form reversal would be no surprise. DELTA ANNE (7) hasn't won for a while, last start finishing seventh here over 1600m, but with the blinkers coming off, she has the ability to bounce back into a top 4 spot in a modest field. SALARY MAN (9) finished fifth, beaten five lengths, over 1920m at York seven-and-a-half weeks ago and with some gear changes, along with a freshen up, he looks well placed to improve. Include in all combos to be safe. ANNA'S BOY (4) turned his form around last time out, and he is another with top claims, especially after drawing in the pole position.
